cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SY. 

The paper focuses on developing a Task-Oriented Grasping Network (TOG-Net) for tool manipulation, which involves reasoning about the desired effect of the task and properly grasping and manipulating the tool to achieve the task. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed model is trained using large-scale simulated self-supervision with procedurally generated tool objects, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the model is tested on real-world experiments, which involves system and control (cs.SY) aspects.
